\fBLCB_CNTL_CONFIG_CACHE_LOADED\fR \fI(int*)\fR
.RS 4
Determines whether the configuration cache (if used) was used\&. If the configuration cache is in use, the argument pointer will be set to a true value\&. If the configuration cache was not used, the argument pointer will be set to false\&.
.sp
A false value may indicates that the client will need to load the configuration from the network\&. This may be caused by the following:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
The configuration cache did not exist or was empty
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
The configuration cache contained stale information
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
int is_loaded;
lcb_cntl(instance, LCB_CNTL_GET,
         LCB_CNTL_CONFIG_CACHE_LOADED, &is_loaded);
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
if (is_loaded) {
    printf("Configuration cache saved us a trip to the config server\en");
} else {
    printf("We had to contact the configuration server for some reason\en");
}
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.RE
.RE
.PP
\fBLCB_CNTL_FORCE_SASL_MECH\fR \fI(char*)\fR, \fI(char **)\fR
.RS 4
Get/Set\&. Force a specific SASL mechanism to use for authentication\&. This can allow a user to ensure a certain level of security and have the connection fail if the desired mechanism is not available\&.
.sp
When setting this value, the arg parameter shall be a NUL\-terminated string or a NULL pointer (to unset)\&. When retrieving this value, the parameter shall be set to a
\fIchar **\fR\&. Note that this value (in LCB_CNTL_GET) is valid only until the next call to a libcouchbase API, after which it may have been freed\&.
.sp
Also note that no validation is done to ensure that the argument is a valid SASL mechanism\&.
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
lcb_cntl(instance, LCB_CNTL_SET, LCB_CNTL_FORCE_SASL_MECH, "PLAIN");
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
char *mech;
lcb_cntl(instance, LCB_CNTL_GET, LCB_CNTL_FORCE_SASL_MECH, &mech);
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
