.PP
\fBLCB_CNTL_MAX_REDIRECTS\fR \fI(int*)\fR
.RS 4
Get/Set\&. Set how many redirects the library should follow for the single request\&. Set to \-1 to remove limit at all\&.
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
int new_value = 5;
lcb_cntl(instance, LCB_CNTL_SET, LCB_CNTL_MAX_REDIRECTS, &new_value);
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.RE
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.sp
LCB_NOT_SUPPORTED if the code is unrecognized LCB_EINVAL if there was a problem with the argument (typically for SET) other error codes depending on the command\&. LCB_EINTERNAL if an internal error occurred\&.
